<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910808-0016</DOCNO><DOCID>910808-0016.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Loews Corp.:   Insurance Investment Gains   Boosted 2nd-Quarter Profit</HL><DATE>08/08/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B2</SO><CO>   LTR</CO><MS>FINANCIAL (FIN)</MS><IN>EARNINGS (ERN)PROPERTY andamp; CASUALTY INSURANCE (INP)INSURANCE (INS)</IN><NS>EARNINGS (ERN)</NS><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)NEW YORK (NY)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Loews Corp. reported sharp increases in second-quarterearnings, on the strength of investment gains in itsinsurance portfolios.   New York-based Loews, which also has interests in hotels,tobacco products and other businesses, said net income forthe period surged about 50% to $290.7 million, or $4.17 ashare, from $192.9 million, or $2.60 a share, a year earlier.</LP><TEXT>   The investment gains amounted to $67.1 million, or 96cents a share, compared with year-earlier investment lossesof $16.8 million, or 23 cents a share.   Loews had second-quarter revenue of $3.45 billion, up 12%from $3.09 billion a year ago.   For the six months, Loews reported net rose 2% to $426.7million, or $6.11 a share, from $416.6 million, or $5.60 ashare, a year earlier. First-half revenue rose 10% to $6.66billion from $6.07 billion a year earlier. The companypurchased almost 900,000 of its common shares during thefirst half and said that, depending on market conditions, itwould buy additional shares from time to time.</TEXT></DOC>